<Review>I am a longtime customer and do enjoy their products. I have spent thousands of dollars on this website between tincture, flowers, and edibles. All other places from which I order regularly include a free gift. This is smart because it lets me learn about new products to order as well as a fun way to encourage me to order again. Kushcab regularly skips sending a gift even though each order is close to 200 dollars, sometimes more. I probably only receive gifts on 1/3 of my orders. I am very displeased and have expressed my dissatisfaction to them in the past. I was told to place another order and they would make up for it in that order. I immediately placed another 200 dollar order and received one small gift instead of the two that should now be included to make up for the mistake and new order. The next order I again received no gift and again was told to place another order. Again, I immediately ordered and received only one small gift. Now, they send no gifts and don't respond to my emails. I plan to take my business elsewhere and implore that you consider this review before placing an order here. <Response>None</Response><Name>Jon Lo</Name><Review>Awesome escape room! Our groups have done about 10 escape rooms and this by far is our top 3. We had no idea what we were getting ourselves into as this is one of three scary escape rooms in San Diego. This was a referral from one of my friends and we just say why the heck not. As we got there we we're briefed and set up into our rooms. Get there early because there are waivers and questions that you might want to ask when you get there. Be sure to ask questions. This escape room is not like the others. They have very good clues and the props were cool. It definitely fits the theme and an extra surprise will be awaiting for you in your rooms. Like the other escape rooms we get three clues. Our host Chris was very entertaining and helpful with the clues. Our group got out with 20:31 to spare. Super fun and highly recommend. <Date>1582480461810< /Date><Response>None< /Response><user_name>D R<//user_name><Gmap_id>0x80dbff95cf2a693d:0x8be7298ce8e92d5d< /Gmap_id><UserId.>109430697243915898701</UserId.></record>

< review>
What a fun night! *Spoiler free review*
My group of 4 booked the 9:30 Harvest Motel room and we were very anxious to begin. Our Game Master Chris welcomed us and made sure we knew all of the rules and the backstory of the room. He then split us into our 4 separate rooms and the game began. The puzzles themselves were not too difficult, they were all things that we had seen before. Even though the puzzles were fairly easy, what kept us on our toes was the and fear of the unknown evil in the room.
Some puzzles do require outside knowledge but you have 3 hints if you need to use one for it. We personally didn't find it an issue because at least one person in our group knew the answer.
The atmosphere kept the room feeling spooky and kept us on edge the whole time. The ending puzzle was a little anti-climactic but with that evil force in there, we just happy to escape it! We got out with 16 minutes left  and felt accomplished. Looking back at it the room wasn't too difficult with was mostly just the part of being separated that made our adrenaline kick in. I would recommend this to groups of 4-8; I think 12 (which is there max booking) would just be too big especially if you book for a group of 4 and then get paired with randoms for the rest.

Overall, the game was fun, thrilling, and a great way to bond.
This was my 46th room, I would recommend this room mostly to beginners but also to enthusiasts who are looking for a spooky separation room game.

Shout out to the Game Master Chris for being awesome and talking with us after the game too, we really appreciated it!<//review>

< Text>
We bought a Groupon for the Hourglass room and arrived about 15 min before game time. Justin was a great game host - very enthusiastic and friendly!
Pros about the game/experience:
*good game for beginners & advanced
*had a nice mix of beginning finds to get the game moving right off
*utilized several media sources (audio, visual, etc) as part of the game
*unique puzzles and challenges
*open weeknights!

Cons about the game:
*parking situation (not directly related to the game though!) was limited. We came in one car, so not too big of an issue but if I had a larger group I am not sure there were enough designated spots for everyone.
*the clues to solve the puzzle in the room weren't intuitive. Meaning we found a clue and it had information, but it wasn't innately clear if the info itself was the clue, or if the info + the object = a puzzle to solve to get the clue. Sorry if that's ambiguous, I'm trying to be vague so I don't give away anything about the game.

We are more of "vets" to the escape game world (though we brought 2 friends who were newbies) and all 4 of us had a great time! The hotel room sounds awesome if you like scary stuff - maybe the hubby will be back for that one! In the meantime, I'm looking forward to if/when they release new rooms (that aren't scary ;) )

Oh! And on the way out Justin offered to let us play the "travel escape game" and it was so cool! That's the first time I've seen a mini-version of an escape room that can all be done on the table top. Great job, 3rd Day Escape! Thank you for a fun night out!<//Text>

< text>
Was a great experience, very friendly staff, creative story line, like the seperation in the rooms in the beginning and have to work your way out to rejoin friends. The set and props were movie like along with music and the alterations of lights increasing the suspense. The puzzles were not impossible but required you to think and when solving certain puzzles, the outcome after solving it was not cheesy, for instance in movies when you lift a book a hidden wall appears (that certain instacne did not happen) and makes it much more realistic like youre in an actual movie.< /text>

< text>
I've done over 10 escape rooms in San Diego and Harvest Motel is by far my favorite one! I came here for my cousin's bachelorette party and it was the perfect way to start the night. We were all terrified in the beginning as you pull in to a creepy looking motel building, but we're so glad we went through with it. Truly immersive experience from beginning to end whixh is what I personally look for in escape rooms. Without giving away too much, this room has a unique format and vibe that is different from anything I have ever done. Can't wait to come back and try their other rooms!!<//text>

<text>Beautiful Venue!!
Had our wedding 10/12/19, could not of asked for a more perfect day. There is something about when you step on the grounds at Springville Ranch...that is peaceful and has such a good vibe. The owners and Debbie went above and beyond in making our day one to remember.  If you are looking for something special for your wedding, this is a must. We used the entire property.. married on the Bridge, cocktail hour at the gazebo,  and reception in the magical barn.  We also stayed on the property Sat night after the wedding. < Review>
Great experience.  Buying ticket on-line was SIMPLE and no hassle.  You do NOT need to print ticket after buying on-line.  When the bus show's up, just show the driver your 'e-ticket' on your phone or computer, they'll scan the barcode that's on there, and it's DONE!  SIMPLE!
And NO baggage 'fee's,' that's WHY you don't need to be concernered with putting tag's on your bag's.
Security was also present and VERY visible, and a pleasure to talk with.
HOWEVER; as much as I appreciate the bus arriving EARLY, it also LEFT EARLY (by TEN minutes).  If your one of those types who like to arrive NINE minutes early ... even BEFORE it's 'schedueled' departure time, you would have been seriously S.O.L.!
You would have found yourself playing 'pick-up-sticks' with a toothless vagrant named 'Bertha' for the next 6-hour's, waiting for the next bus, wondering, "If only."< /Review>

<Review>I started my journey April 2016 and by the end of July I lost about 17 lbs...I started eating what ever I wanted on weekends and stopped losing weight...I maintained my weight up until the end of October that's because I stopped going to the bootcamp and I stopped my nutrition as well...I gained almost all my weight back and talked to Richard about wanting to come back and he encouraged me to go back...I started the bootcamp again the end of February 2017...On my day back I talked to coach Michael and told him my struggle...he helped me find the motivation that I was lacking before and he keeps me on track and tells me as I am working out the reason why I am trying to better myself...So far I have lost 36lbs and I am 2 lbs away from my initial goal I had set for myself last year...My starting weight in February was 173lbs and as of today 137lbs...The best part of the bootcamp is the environment...Everyone is a teamplayer and we will help motivate each other...Thank you Richard for giving us different meal plans to help reach our goals and for answering all my nutritional questions...Thank you coach Michael for helping me reach my goal...I honestly don't think I could have done this AMAZING weight loss without your support and thanks for pushing me through my workout when I am wanting to stop...Coach Sandy thanks for pushing me through the workouts and for doing them with me when I have wanted to stop...This bootcamp has HONESTLY made me Strongerüí™, Leaner and most importantly it made me love Myself ‚ù§</Review><gmap_id>0x80c36623013fdfc9:0x9d6fe46bcac04fe3< /gmap_id><Time>1498334594275<//Time></record></dataset><record>

They were prompt in scheduling the move out walk through,  but my deposit is nearly a month late at this point. I've followed up countless times by phone and email, only to be ignored or refereed to someone else who is just as unhelpful.

In short, you can count on them to be on top of anything pertaining to their direct interests, but if you need assistance or are owed anything, don't hold your breathe.<//text>
